  m_text: In the Natalis VR simulation, hand tracking allows users to interact seamlessly
    with the virtual environment without the need for controllers. Using your hands,
    you can engage with UI elements, manipulate objects, and navigate through the
    simulation. The guide provides essential tips on how to use hand tracking to
    interact with buttons, tools, and other in-simulation features, making the experience
    more immersive and intuitive.
